					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-763804#post-2699140</guid>
				<title>Awesome</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-763804/scp-1765#post-2699140</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 29 Nov 2016 01:09:58 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>goodyfresh</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1643572</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is simply a fantastic take on the idea of the Fates. I love it. I still can't make up my mind as to whether they really do think they're being helpful in their own way, or (seems more likely) they are just screwing with the Foundation for kicks.</p> <p>Seems like the latter is more likely, as basically the Foundation's entire purpose is to defy fate (the fate of humanity to be overcome by anomalies). Seems like something the Fates themselves would be pissed about.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-763804#post-2576054</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
